items.title: Dogecoin rebounds 3% as Elon Musk backs down from feud with Trump
items.description: The Tesla CEO said that he regrets some of his posts about the president last week.

items.title: The global oil and gas industry is ‘deteriorating,’ says top credit ratings agency
items.description: Fitch lowered its 2025 rating of the global oil sector from "neutral" to "deteriorating."

items.title: Starbucks’ new game plan to roll out AI chatbots at cafes could serve as a ‘litmus test’ for the industry, analyst says
items.description: The coffee chain will deploy the OpenAI-powered tech in 35 stores before rolling it out nationwide in the fall.

items.title: ‘Buffy’ star Sarah Michelle Gellar hates writing big checks—she cuts coupons, researches gas prices before filling up, and stares at purchases ‘for days’ before buying
items.description: Other stars like Keke Palmer and Ed Sheeran prefer low-cost lifestyles, setting budgets, crashing at people’s houses, and living below their means.

items.title: Cathie Wood’s ARK Invest predicts SpaceX will be worth $2.5 trillion by 2030—and the key to Elon Musk’s Mars ambitions will be Starlink
items.description: That valuation would represent a 38% annualized return from SpaceX’s $350 billion funding round in December.
